President Samia Suluhu Hassan has appointed Nehemia Mchechu as the new Treasury Registrar replacing Mgonya Benedicto who will be assigned to other duties. Prior to the appointment, Mr Mchechu was the Director of the National Housing Corporation (NHC). To fill the Mchechu’s vacuum, a statement issued by the Director of Presidential Communications; Zuhura Yunus on Friday says the Head of State has also appointed Hamad Abdallah as the Director General of NHC. Prior to his new role, Mr Abdallah was the Managing Director of Giamcoafrica Limited. Moreover, the President appointed Mussa Mohamed Makame as the Executive Director of the Tanzania Petroleum Development Corporation (TPDC). He is replacing Dr James Mataragio who will be assigned to other duties, according to the statement. Prior to his appointment, Makame was a member of the TPDC board. Makame is a leading consultant in Tanzania’s oil and gas industry. All appointments are effective from today, Friday.